A worker came to fix the kitchen floor, and I pretended I was just working from home, but I was actually editing "Addicted".
If this damned file could just open... (OneDrive is absolutely terrible.)
*hacker's voice* I'm in.
He started drilling, and the noise was super loud. Great.
Turned the air purifier to the highest setting; it felt a bit too aggressive, but I did smell wood shavings, so it's justified. Plus, he opposed wearing a mask. And I do need to protect myself, right?
I really want to go back to sleep, but I can't sleep until he leaves.
Good news is, Chapter 4 is finally edited!
Chapter 5 is super long and really anxiety-inducing. Yay! It's so exciting.
Searching and replacing...➡️ ellipses, there are 54 in this chapter😅
But I still insist on this point. Most natural languages are incoherent, especially when people are emotionally excited.
The floor repairman is using a vacuum cleaner to clean up, which I hope means he is almost done.
He went out (it sounds like) he is cutting something. I secretly checked the progress. There is still a lot of work to be done :(
There are still 7 pages left in Chapter 5. This is still my favorite chapter, and the manuscript is in quite good condition, mainly requiring layout adjustments and some minor revisions for active voice and conciseness. But I really need to take a break, have a cup of tea, while that guy is still busy in my kitchen.
He started using the vacuum cleaner again. I hope this is a good omen.
The worker who was repairing the kitchen floor has left!
He told me that he quoted the price for repairing the entire floor, but the landlord is too cheap and only willing to pay for the repair of the area near the door that's already rotten. Feels much better.
I'm drinking tea in the garden, and the air purifier is working hard in the kitchen, purifying the air in the room!
